page.title: 12Ecology
page.content: Borne woods has two entrances one from Swanley,one from Paul's hill.Borne woods has a big scrambling track which is used offically and unoffically.There is also a clay pigeon shoot this happens every month.Running through Borne woods is a railway track to Margate from Swanley.Borne woods is next to Hockenden farm.There is a Motorway,the M3,running just outside the woods. Hockenden woods is a large wood with a naturlist camp.In the north direction in lower Hockenden farm.East of the camp is Hockenden house.South is a railway track,then Sheepcote farm.To the West is a travellers camp.
